So it would lead me to believe that because the shelves open just till dawn, they're probably not going to put lights down there until we get special approval from the DCI.

445
00:30:12,335 --> 00:30:14,816
So we sent 15 resolutions on the same subject matter.

446
00:30:15,256 --> 00:30:17,697
I pushed the internet, and they came up with a contract.

447
00:30:17,817 --> 00:30:20,778
So I just think that it gives us another unique opportunity, Mr. President.

448
00:30:20,798 --> 00:30:22,058
I'm not asking to do it with everything.

449
00:30:22,098 --> 00:30:29,000
I'm asking to do it with the resolutions that have gone forward from 2014 to date, just the resolutions from 2014 that have gone unresponded.

450
00:30:29,020 --> 00:30:32,301
And let's try it out and see if we can do something different and get a better result than what we're getting.

451
00:30:32,781 --> 00:30:33,081
Thank you.

452
00:30:34,542 --> 00:30:34,922
Counselor?

453
00:30:35,642 --> 00:30:36,542
Madam Vice President.

454
00:30:37,363 --> 00:30:47,346
No, I just think what Councilor Marks has merit to, I think we should obviously get responses and we should be on the mayor to respond to our resolutions.

455
00:30:47,426 --> 00:30:53,568
But I also think, you know, it is partly our duty to follow up and to make sure our resolutions are getting responded to.

456
00:30:53,648 --> 00:30:58,590
So this is a way, another avenue, number one, to push the mayor, number two, to follow up on our own.

457
00:30:59,570 --> 00:31:02,931
I think the mayor's got the administration's got away with it for

458
00:31:03,780 --> 00:31:13,346
so long, and every time we bring up the matter and try to get on top of the administration, they'll start responding to more and more, and then kind of fall back and then start again.

459
00:31:13,486 --> 00:31:19,230
So I think this is just another avenue to take it into our own hands and get the resolves answered.

460
00:31:19,930 --> 00:31:21,811
So I think, you know, both counselors are right.

461
00:31:21,991 --> 00:31:22,692
We need to do both.

462
00:31:23,252 --> 00:31:31,577
Mr. President, just if I could, you know, it's this council that takes a vote on whether we send a paper.

463
00:31:31,597 --> 00:31:32,718
It has to be a majority vote.

464
00:31:32,990 --> 00:31:41,274
to the mayor, or whether we set up a committee of the whole meeting, or whether we send it to subcommittee, it's always this council that takes the vote.

465
00:31:41,374 --> 00:31:54,380
So whatever has made its way to the mayor in the year 2014, which the councilor is talking about, was a majority vote of this council, saying we feel that this paper needs to go to the mayor for action.

466
00:31:55,471 --> 00:32:01,494
Now, if the council decided, you know what, we don't feel that's the best avenue to send it to the mayor first.

467
00:32:01,774 --> 00:32:03,254
We rather send it to subcommittee.

468
00:32:03,614 --> 00:32:10,918
Then it's under the purview of this council, which we do on many occasions, send it to subcommittee or committee the whole.

469
00:32:10,958 --> 00:32:17,680
So I'm not, I'm still not quite sure taking a paper back that the mayor has not responded to.

470
00:32:18,221 --> 00:32:20,682
And, and I might add a response.

471
00:32:20,842 --> 00:32:23,563
And I had a discussion just recently with the city solicitor.

472
00:32:24,043 --> 00:32:28,106
A response of, I will take this under advisement, is a response.

473
00:32:28,966 --> 00:32:31,688
You may not like the response, but it's a response.

474
00:32:32,669 --> 00:32:37,432
If the mayor comes back and say, this is something I'm going to be working on, that's also a response.

475
00:32:37,752 --> 00:32:40,814
And we could go back and say, Mr. Mayor, we'd like to know what a time frame is.

476
00:32:41,254 --> 00:32:42,915
You know, the 10 days no longer applies.

477
00:32:43,255 --> 00:32:45,717
How long you think you'll be working on this for?

478
00:32:46,097 --> 00:32:48,539
So there is that dialogue that could take place.

479
00:32:49,484 --> 00:32:59,586
I would just hate to see that this open up an avenue that the mayor, or not this mayor, or the next mayor, whoever it might be, say, you know what?

480
00:33:00,346 --> 00:33:03,286
The city chart is requiring me to respond within 10 days.

481
00:33:03,767 --> 00:33:11,068
However, if I don't, the council's just going to take the paper back, they're going to send it to a subcommittee, and good luck to them.

482
00:33:11,448 --> 00:33:12,688
See what happens with that paper.

483
00:33:13,588 --> 00:33:17,469
The slippery slope also is, and I'm not saying this will happen,

484
00:33:17,973 --> 00:33:36,097
If I had an issue that was near and dear to me, and it gets sent to the subcommittee that Councilor Caviello sits on, along with two other members of the council, and they're not quite that hip on that issue that I'm hip on, that could sit in a burial for months and years in that subcommittee.

485
00:33:36,517 --> 00:33:39,178
And I would have really no input on getting it out.

486
00:33:39,858 --> 00:33:46,300
And I'm not saying that's going to happen, but it would lend itself to that type of activity.

487
00:33:48,463 --> 00:33:57,649
I think the process that's in place, which was created by our forefathers of the city charter, definitely needs to be reviewed.

488
00:33:57,669 --> 00:34:03,472
And I've been one of the most active members of this council calling for a review of the city charter.

489
00:34:03,832 --> 00:34:08,975
And I've publicly stated what I think needs to be changed in the charter that hasn't been looked at.

490
00:34:09,355 --> 00:34:10,735
in 28 years.

491
00:34:11,495 --> 00:34:16,536
I mean, what other document would you say that you established 28 years ago is still valid?

492
00:34:16,936 --> 00:34:21,057
I mean, no business plan would run on a business plan from 28 years ago.

493
00:34:21,797 --> 00:34:38,820
No private corporation or entity would work on such a plan, but the city of Method has, in my opinion, has failed to look at the city charter in the past 28 years to bring it up to a day and age that we all know technology

494
00:34:39,277 --> 00:34:41,098
and many other advances have taken place.

495
00:34:41,598 --> 00:34:45,559
So, you know, I appreciate what Councilman Light brings up.

496
00:34:45,859 --> 00:34:51,161
I think it's part of the frustration that's been behind this reel on getting answers and so forth.

497
00:34:51,701 --> 00:34:55,343
I just don't like that particular avenue of getting to that approach.

498
00:34:55,823 --> 00:35:01,485
I think, honestly, whether it's this mayor or a future mayor, we have to follow the city charter.

499
00:35:01,525 --> 00:35:05,406
And as it reads right now, within 10 days, we should get a response.

500
00:35:06,106 --> 00:35:08,347
And I'm not going to go against the city charter.

501
00:35:08,727 --> 00:35:12,589
If that's the rule, then whoever the mayor is should adhere to that rule.

502
00:35:12,869 --> 00:35:18,553
And if they're not, maybe this council should stand up and take a vote of no confidence and say, you know what?

503
00:35:18,893 --> 00:35:20,514
You're not adhering to the city charter.

504
00:35:20,934 --> 00:35:22,575
We're not happy with the Mr. Mayor.

505
00:35:23,235 --> 00:35:26,637
This is a vote of no confidence to let you know things better change.

506
00:35:27,217 --> 00:35:33,641
But to say, you know what, we'll just take the paper back and scurried into a subcommittee, uh, and let them work on it.

507
00:35:34,322 --> 00:35:36,803
You know, it was sent to the mayor for a reason.

508
00:35:37,242 --> 00:35:39,663
I'm not quite sure that I can support that tonight.

509
00:35:40,503 --> 00:36:06,073
I would ask that we don't take a vote on this tonight and possibly this may be an issue that we want to discuss before one of the rules committee or one of the subcommittees that we have already established before we come up with such a major, it may seem like a minor piece of legislation, but it has a major profound impact on how this council runs and how we get

510
00:36:06,497 --> 00:36:09,338
questions and answers from the administration, Mr. President.

511
00:36:10,078 --> 00:36:10,979
Thank you, Counselor.

512
00:36:11,279 --> 00:36:16,340
So on the motion of approval by Counselors Knight and Longo Kern, Counselor Carvialho.

513
00:36:16,540 --> 00:36:17,421
Thank you, Mr. President.

514
00:36:17,521 --> 00:36:19,021
I agree with Counselor Marks on this.

515
00:36:19,682 --> 00:36:29,465
I mean, if anything needs to go to a subcommittee, I think this rule does because, like I said, this has an effect on our charter and the way we do business here.

516
00:36:29,505 --> 00:36:35,307
So I think before we vote on this this evening, again, whether we go to the Rules Committee,

517
00:36:36,237 --> 00:36:41,782
This is something that I think needs a little more discussion so we know that we're going in the right direction with this.

518
00:36:42,282 --> 00:36:45,444
And like I said, it is up to the mayor to respond within 10 days.

519
00:36:45,484 --> 00:36:52,350
And hey, let's say, if it's something near and dear to me, I'm going to be on the mayor's phone saying, hey, where is it?

520
00:36:52,390 --> 00:36:53,010
Let's get it going.

521
00:36:54,171 --> 00:36:56,613
That's part of our job to do our diligence.

522
00:36:57,313 --> 00:37:04,499
Something that's near and dear to our heart, then get on the mayor and get him to move on it.

523
00:37:06,083 --> 00:37:07,104
Thank you, Councilor Cavillo.

524
00:37:07,144 --> 00:37:07,644
Councilor Knight.

525
00:37:08,705 --> 00:37:15,070
Again, Mr. President, like I said, the definition of insanity is doing the same thing over and over again and expecting a different result.

526
00:37:15,950 --> 00:37:23,156
Obviously, week in and week out, we have the same people with the same complaints about lack of response from the administration, lack of respect from the administration.

527
00:37:23,616 --> 00:37:35,365
I looked at this as a new and creative way for us to approach the way that we do business here, to take ownership of the issues that we send forward, to actually roll up our sleeves and get to work, dig down and figure it out, what's going on, talk with the department heads, talk with the people that are there on the ground,

528
00:37:35,662 --> 00:37:37,783
that on the ground level doing this type of work, Mr. President.

529
00:37:37,803 --> 00:37:39,183
So that's where I'm coming from.

530
00:37:39,323 --> 00:37:46,665
Again, you know, I've been on the council now for a little bit over a year, and I haven't seen any proposal that would, you know, suggest that we change the way that we're doing business.

531
00:37:47,245 --> 00:37:51,746
However, I've also sat here and I've listened to the same complaints week in and week out about the frustrations that people have.

532
00:37:52,106 --> 00:37:59,328
I'm trying to come up with a solution to a problem, a problem that I feel as though is hindering the ability of this body to move forward and to act effectively.

533
00:37:59,468 --> 00:38:01,869
So that's why I brought the resolution forward, Mr. President.

534
00:38:01,889 --> 00:38:02,529
I'd ask for a roll call.

535
00:38:03,029 --> 00:38:03,330
Thank you.

536
00:38:04,010 --> 00:38:04,950
Mr. President,

537
00:38:06,329 --> 00:38:07,210
Councilor Marks.

538
00:38:08,291 --> 00:38:10,032
There's a thing called accountability too.

539
00:38:11,013 --> 00:38:30,309
And I think we have to keep that in mind that, um, you know, uh, under the charter, the mayors accountable to respond back to this council and to remove that accountability, uh, and say that, uh, you know what, it's not important that the mayor respond back to us because we'll just take back any response we already sent to them and send it to a subcommittee.

540
00:38:30,629 --> 00:38:33,952
I think sends the wrong message, not only to the members of this council,

541
00:38:34,302 --> 00:38:38,185
but to the entire community itself that the process is broken right now.

542
00:38:38,765 --> 00:38:50,293
And I can tell you as one member, the mayor came back to us several months back saying that if the council was interested in a dog park, they said, the mayor said, go out and find funding.

543
00:38:51,072 --> 00:38:52,774
I took the ball, Mr. President.

544
00:38:53,154 --> 00:38:54,095
I ran with the ball.

545
00:38:54,475 --> 00:38:55,836
I organized my own committee.

546
00:38:56,137 --> 00:38:56,597
We went out.

547
00:38:56,657 --> 00:38:58,178
We found funding for a dog park.

548
00:38:58,619 --> 00:39:03,423
So I know how to get things done in the community, and I know how to pick up a phone.

549
00:39:03,443 --> 00:39:04,604
I've been doing this for a long time.

550
00:39:04,964 --> 00:39:13,132
I talked to the department heads, but we all know under the city charter, there's one chief executive officer in this community, and he controls

551
00:39:13,850 --> 00:39:32,356
a lot of the strings and what goes on in this community, and we need his input, and we need his support, and to, I think, create an environment that the council will work in its own vacuum, and the mayor will do whatever he wants to do, and that's not the way city government should operate.

552
00:39:32,916 --> 00:39:43,400
And I don't think, I think it's well-intended, this resolution, but I don't think it suits any purpose other than, honestly, just lip service, and it's not gonna, in my opinion,

553
00:39:43,766 --> 00:39:45,407
do anything to improve the process.

554
00:39:45,828 --> 00:39:49,390
If anything, it's going to hamper the communications between the administration.

555
00:39:49,770 --> 00:39:56,475
So at this point, Mr. President, I would, after the gentleman speaks, I would respectfully ask that this issue be tabled.

556
00:40:00,579 --> 00:40:03,080
I'll remove it until the gentleman speaks then, Mr. President.

557
00:40:04,041 --> 00:40:05,402
Motion is withdrawn.

558
00:40:07,364 --> 00:40:09,245
Sir, please state your name and address for the record.

559
00:40:09,773 --> 00:40:12,194
Michael Ruggiero, I live on 18 Pembroke Street.

560
00:40:13,214 --> 00:40:23,476
While I appreciate the frustration that has led to this motion, I strongly suggest that you neither table this resolution nor vote yes for it.

561
00:40:25,516 --> 00:40:36,659
This council, if so many resolutions have gone to the mayor and the mayor has ignored them, this council is complicit in

562
00:40:37,505 --> 00:40:41,648
enabling an administration that prefers procrastination to action.

563
00:40:43,029 --> 00:40:50,553
I urge you, do not simply just re-look at things that you've already gone through and don't table this.

564
00:40:51,654 --> 00:40:57,357
Do not allow the mayor's office to coast into the end of its term.

565
00:40:58,138 --> 00:41:02,641
There is too much important work that must be done in Medford.

566
00:41:04,162 --> 00:41:05,923
I respectfully suggest

567
00:41:06,665 --> 00:41:22,050
that perhaps the resolution should be, if the mayor does not respond to all 23, if that is the right, 20-some number of unresponded resolutions, then a vote of non-confidence will immediately follow.

568
00:41:23,530 --> 00:41:30,713
And also for transparency, may I ask that all of the unresponded resolutions be read.

569
00:41:31,413 --> 00:41:31,713
Thank you.

