730
00:53:21,785 --> 00:53:40,651
appear before the Memphis City Council along with some neighbors regarding 59 Boynton Road, a home that's been in terrible condition and been marked by the city as a home that should not be entered in disrepair.

731
00:53:41,591 --> 00:53:49,574
We as a council asked for opinions from the city solicitor on a number of issues from the Board of Health, Karen Rose.

732
00:53:50,104 --> 00:53:54,707
and also Paul Mokey, the building commissioner, regarding what the next steps are on the property.

733
00:53:55,448 --> 00:54:10,958
And I just want people to know that we did receive a lengthy and thorough explanation regarding many of our questions in our packet this week from Paul Mokey, the building commissioner, Karen Rose, and the city solicitor, Mark Rumley.

734
00:54:11,639 --> 00:54:18,984
And according to my discussions recently with Mark, he thinks that the court process

735
00:54:19,962 --> 00:54:22,004
is probably going to be another six to eight weeks.

736
00:54:23,565 --> 00:54:48,284
And hopefully after that, Mr. President, when all the court issues are ironed out, that we'll be able to move forward with the seal of that property and eventually the either knocking the property down or the refurbishing of the home, if possible, to help out with the neighborhood and the residents that have to live alongside that eyesore

737
00:54:48,882 --> 00:54:50,604
and public safety concern in their neighborhood.

738
00:54:50,624 --> 00:54:56,649
So I just wanted to give an update on that property, Mr. President, and hopefully we can move forward.

739
00:54:57,209 --> 00:54:59,871
Thank you very much, Councilor Moxx, for that kind update.

